This paper discusses the use of machine learning in compiler optimization, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also covers concepts related to machine learning such as features, models, training, and deployment, which are commonly studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the survey and roadmap of different research areas, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper also discusses open issues and potential research directions, which are relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY).
